Change the reporting date and pull the report.
Create the reporting group and pull the report.
Change the reporting metric and pull the report.
Setup API Credentials for connecting to PH.
tell application "Alfred 3" to run trigger "ph:setupNetworkKey" in workflow "com.codable.us.phparser"
tell application "Alfred 3" to run trigger "ph:setupUserKey" in workflow "com.codable.us.phparser"
tell application "Alfred 3" to run trigger "ph:setupDomain" in workflow "com.codable.us.phparser"
tell application "Alfred 3" to run trigger "ph:validateCredentials" in workflow "com.codable.us.phparser"
Provide your api sub-domain, most likely "api".
Querying the API to see if your credentials are valid.
Prepare reporting parameters for making API calls.
tell application "Alfred 3" to run trigger "ph:setupReport" in workflow "com.codable.us.phparser"
Are you going to report as an advertiser or publisher?
tell application "Alfred 3" to run trigger "ph:prepareReportID" in workflow "com.codable.us.phparser"
tell application "Alfred 3" to run trigger "ph:prepareReportMetrics" in workflow "com.codable.us.phparser"
Provide the ID you want to report on. Could take a minute to load.
Provide the metric you want to report on, clicks or conversions.
tell application "Alfred 3" to run trigger "ph:prepareReportStatus" in workflow "com.codable.us.phparser"
Provide the statuses you want to report on for conversions.
tell application "Alfred 3" to run trigger "ph:prepareReportDate" in workflow "com.codable.us.phparser"
tell application "Alfred 3" to run trigger "ph:downloadReport" in workflow "com.codable.us.phparser"
Provide the dates you want to report on using contextual means.
do shell script "killall Growl && open -a Growl"

set haveDate to "{query}"
if haveDate = "TRUE" then tell application "Alfred 3" to run trigger "ph:downloadReport" in workflow "com.codable.us.phparser" else
tell application "System Events" set isRunning to (count of (every process whose bundle identifier is "com.Growl.GrowlHelperApp")) > 0 end tell
if isRunning then tell application id "com.Growl.GrowlHelperApp" set the allNotificationsList to ¬ {"Invalid API Response!", "Invalid API Response!"}
set the enabledNotificationsList to ¬ {"Invalid API Response!"}
register as application ¬ "Growl AppleScript Sample" all notifications allNotificationsList ¬ default notifications enabledNotificationsList ¬ icon of application "Script Editor"
notify with name ¬ "Invalid API Response!" title ¬ "Invalid API Response!" description ¬ "You must re-configure the report parameters." application name "Growl AppleScript Sample"
end tell else display notification "You must re-configure the report parameters." with title "Invalid API Response!" end if
tell application "Alfred 3" to run trigger "ph:setupReport" in workflow "com.codable.us.phparser" end if

set hasFile to "{query}"
if hasFile = "TRUE" then tell application "Alfred 3" to run trigger "ph:showReport" in workflow "com.codable.us.phparser" else
tell application "System Events" set isRunning to (count of (every process whose bundle identifier is "com.Growl.GrowlHelperApp")) > 0 end tell
if isRunning then tell application id "com.Growl.GrowlHelperApp" set the allNotificationsList to ¬ {"Invalid API Response!", "Invalid API Response!"}
set the enabledNotificationsList to ¬ {"Invalid API Response!"}
register as application ¬ "Growl AppleScript Sample" all notifications allNotificationsList ¬ default notifications enabledNotificationsList ¬ icon of application "Script Editor"
notify with name ¬ "Invalid API Response!" title ¬ "Invalid API Response!" description ¬ "You must re-configure the report parameters." application name "Growl AppleScript Sample"
end tell else display notification "You must re-configure the report parameters." with title "Invalid API Response!" end if
tell application "Alfred 3" to run trigger "ph:setupReport" in workflow "com.codable.us.phparser" end if

set theQuery to POSIX file "{query}"
tell application "Finder" to open theQuery
tell application "Alfred 3" to run trigger "ph:downloadReport" in workflow "com.codable.us.phparser"

The first things you need to run is:
“ph auth”
This will allow you to set up your credentials. You can then run:
“ph report”
This will allow you to configure basic (at this time) settings for the API call. Once you are complete, it will allow you to download it automatically. You can re-download the file any time by running:
“ph download”
Since this uses contextual dates it really leverages the power of being able to get refreshed data instantly. For more information on the PH API see:
http://apidocs.performancehorizon.com/index.php?title=API_Documentation
Thanks!
Cris Griffith
